The rating agency says the decision was taken on the back of political and institutional uncertainty. JOHANNESBURG Standard &amp; Poor s global has just announced South Africa's sovereign credit rating has been downgraded to double B plus.The rating agency says the decision has been taken on the back of political and institutional uncertainty.Fears of a downgrade were raised last week already when President Jacob Zuma announced his Cabinet reshuffle in which Pravin Gordhan was axed.More to follow on this developing story . (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)